00:30:34.858 --> 00:30:41.426
That bitterness took root and it defiled everyone in this generation, but just a few men and a few families.

00:30:42.434 --> 00:30:44.157
They did not enter into God's rest.

00:30:44.477 --> 00:31:06.994
Friend, if you let it be a warning this morning, if you don't deal with that bitterness in your heart, if you don't let that, if you don't grow in the grace of God and experience the grace of God in Christ, and if you don't let that overflow and overcome the bitterness and the hatred that you have in your heart and may it be in my heart, friend, you and I will end up just like Judas, Judas who was disappointed in Christ.

00:31:07.266 --> 00:31:12.093
that Christ did not come to rule the way he expected him to rule to take over Jerusalem.

00:31:12.273 --> 00:31:15.958
At the moment he thought he was going to do it with all the power of mind he's seen in Christ.

00:31:15.978 --> 00:31:17.620
He was disappointed with Christ.

00:31:17.640 --> 00:31:20.604
And therefore he foresuck Christ and bitterness set up in his heart.

00:31:20.945 --> 00:31:22.226
And you see how that story ended.

00:31:22.707 --> 00:31:25.651
Friend, that story and that story will be you and me.

00:31:25.791 --> 00:31:33.342
If we don't figure out how to deal with bitterness in our heart, we will not enter into the rest of God.

00:31:33.362 --> 00:31:36.626
The Christian cannot keep bitterness in their heart.

00:31:36.738 --> 00:31:39.682
Let this be a warning, lest the plagues of Egypt fall upon us.

00:31:41.324 --> 00:31:50.297
Verse 27, they come to Elam where there were 12 springs of water and 70 palm trees, and they had camped there by the water.

00:31:50.317 --> 00:31:51.659
Now, they came to an Oasis.

